trans-unit.source: Wait a minute and click Refresh.
trans-unit.target: Wait a minute and click Refresh.

trans-unit.source: The charts refresh themselves periodically, but you can also refresh manually.
trans-unit.target: The charts refresh themselves periodically, but you can also refresh manually.

trans-unit.source: The refresh interval depends on the time range of the chart.

trans-unit.source: Check that you have an instrumentation key defined in the ApplicationInsights.xml file (in the resources folder in your project)
trans-unit.target: Check that you have an instrumentation key defined in the ApplicationInsights.xml file (in the resources folder in your project)

trans-unit.source: Verify that there is no `<DisableTelemetry>true</DisableTelemetry>` node in the xml file.
trans-unit.target: Verify that there is no `<DisableTelemetry>true</DisableTelemetry>` node in the xml file.

trans-unit.source: In your firewall, you might have to open TCP ports 80 and 443 for outgoing traffic to dc.services.visualstudio.com and f5.services.visualstudio.com.
trans-unit.target: In your firewall, you might have to open TCP ports 80 and 443 for outgoing traffic to dc.services.visualstudio.com and f5.services.visualstudio.com.

trans-unit.source: In the Microsoft Azure start board, look at the service status map.
trans-unit.target: In the Microsoft Azure start board, look at the service status map.

trans-unit.source: If there are some alert indications, wait until they have returned to OK and then close and re-open your Application Insights application blade.
trans-unit.target: If there are some alert indications, wait until they have returned to OK and then close and re-open your Application Insights application blade.

trans-unit.source: Turn on logging to the IDE console window, by adding an `<SDKLogger />` element under the root node in the ApplicationInsights.xml file (in the resources folder in your project), and check for entries prefaced with [Error].
trans-unit.target: Turn on logging to the IDE console window, by adding an `<SDKLogger />` element under the root node in the ApplicationInsights.xml file (in the resources folder in your project), and check for entries prefaced with [Error].

trans-unit.source: Make sure that the correct ApplicationInsights.xml file has been successfully loaded by the Java SDK, by looking at the console's output messages for a "Configuration file has been successfully found" statement.
trans-unit.target: Make sure that the correct ApplicationInsights.xml file has been successfully loaded by the Java SDK, by looking at the console's output messages for a "Configuration file has been successfully found" statement.

trans-unit.source: If the config file is not found, check the output messages to see where the config file is being searched for, and make sure that the ApplicationInsights.xml is located in one of those search locations.
trans-unit.target: If the config file is not found, check the output messages to see where the config file is being searched for, and make sure that the ApplicationInsights.xml is located in one of those search locations.

trans-unit.source: As a rule of thumb, you can place the config file near the Application Insights SDK JARs.
trans-unit.target: As a rule of thumb, you can place the config file near the Application Insights SDK JARs.

trans-unit.source: For example: in Tomcat, this would mean the WEB-INF/lib folder.
trans-unit.target: For example: in Tomcat, this would mean the WEB-INF/lib folder.

trans-unit.source: How can I change which Azure resource my project sends data to?
trans-unit.target: How can I change which Azure resource my project sends data to?

trans-unit.source: [Get the instrumentation key of the new resource.][java]
trans-unit.target: [Get the instrumentation key of the new resource.][java]

trans-unit.source: If you added Application Insights to your project using the Azure Toolkit for Eclipse, right click your web project, select **Azure**, **Configure Application Insights**, and change the key.
trans-unit.target: If you added Application Insights to your project using the Azure Toolkit for Eclipse, right click your web project, select **Azure**, **Configure Application Insights**, and change the key.

trans-unit.source: Otherwise, update the key in ApplicationInsights.xml in the resources folder in your project.
trans-unit.target: Otherwise, update the key in ApplicationInsights.xml in the resources folder in your project.
